content:
Example 1:
Text: Hi Elen. Are you aware that you are currently listed at <url> as inactive?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 2:
Text: ...just vandalized my page again. What level warning is appropriate?
Annotation from annotator: 4

Example 3:
Text: Does anything populate <url>? What is this category for, precisely?
Annotation from annotator: 15

Example 4:
Text: He has now switched from controversially closing AfDs to controversially tagging every episode in TV series (currently ''Heroes'' and ''Star Trek'') with Notability tags. Is this user in need of a block to let him know that WP is not about making points to others based on our own personal opinions?
Annotation from annotator: 11

Example 5:
Text: I have an email from the owner of this image that your BOT deleted.  Can you please restore this and I can send in the email granting me permission to post?
Annotation from annotator: 17

Example 6:
Text: Because I haven't seen it; I'm not even sure from the discussion whether it's on or off Wikipedia. Can you supply a link or a reference?
Annotation from annotator: 15

Example 7:
Text: , and <url> hot. What more could a young man need?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 8:
Text: I tagged the most recent article. Aren't there guidelines for public history in your state?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 9:
Text: What's up with all those tweaky changes?  Just salting redirects?
Annotation from annotator: 4

Example 10:
Text: Counter offer, work in a sandpit and if we can't agree, review in a week.  What do you say?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 11:
Text: See my comment on the talk page. How did this ever get to DYK?
Annotation from annotator: 18

Example 12:
Text: DONE. Do you think everything is now sorted so I can beep Brain Boulton?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 13:
Text: He published the document himself for the world to see. What privacy?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 14:
Text: Hello Jeffq, I noticed you revert vandalism occasionally. Would you like me to grant your account <url> to help you revert vandalism more easily?
Annotation from annotator: 24

Example 15:
Text: Hey, what do you think if instead of naming surahs like this <url>, we add the surah number to each like : "Surah 1, Al-Fatiha". Would u agree with such page moves?
Annotation from annotator: 17

Example 16:
Text: I just traced an IP you just blocked for six months, <url>, and it is a school IP. Is this block an anonymous only block, or is it a full block?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 17:
Text: Hi Fropuff. How do you convert your commutative diagrams from LaTeX to PNG?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 18:
Text: Clever devil.  Do you eat picalilli in Scotland or is that a Brit thing?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 19:
Text: I think I'm gonna request a free image from a Wikipedia biography subject by following <url>. I was wondering, if I'm planning to upload the image to Commons and the subject doesn't speak English to understand the e-mail, what should I do?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 20:
Text: I hope I am now signed on and you remove the erroneous vandalism report. Don't you think it would be more politic to send a message with a question than to preemptorily declare an edit "vandalism"?
Annotation from annotator: 15

Example 21:
Text: While browsing wikipedia for missing pages to write i saw it on your things to do list. Assuming he's a poet, do you mean <url>?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 22:
Text: how do you know that Yuvan is confirmed for Striker? You indeed referring to the <url> starring Siddharth?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 23:
Text: Thanks for doing the tidy up on the SSC page.  One question, what was the reason for removing the item about the Simon PG ownership of the buildings, as well as dropping the link to the company's WP entry?
Annotation from annotator: 18

Example 24:
Text: While editing the COIN page regarding Ciplex, I accidently broke your sig. Since I don't want any more flame, could you please fix it?
Annotation from annotator: 18

Example 25:
Text: The large coat of arms is still be commented on. Maybe you can lend a word or two?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 26:
Text: Rather than tell me how wrong I was to close certain afd's maybe your time would be better spent dealing with the current afd backlog <url>. If my decisions were so wrong why haven't you re-opened them?
Annotation from annotator: 7

Example 27:
Text: I permit myself to bring your attention about the edits of <url> (16 november) who is removing the name <url> from all the articles of wikipedia. What can be done ?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 28:
Text: Why is ''<url>'' a better name for this page than ''<url>'', which has now been made a redirect page?  Is it not standard to speak of "great circle distance"?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 29:
Text: Just saw your edit on <url>. Could you tell me how does Croatian Glagolitic differ from other Glagolitics?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 30:
Text: There are many articles without an infobox image because nobody has found a free alternative. Wasn't there one of Singer at Comic-Con ages ago?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Text: Thanks for the alert.  By the way, how's Granny doing?
Annotation from annotator:
